cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as summarization. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a neural network-based approach for summarization. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing models that can generate summaries similar to human-written ones. It could also be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as summarization is a common task in this field. Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it proposes a novel neural network architecture for summarization.
